cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper presents a new algorithm for multi-class classification using Support Vector Machines. The algorithm relies on data sparsity in high dimensional space and performs a smart partitioning of the whole training data set into disjoint subsets that are easily separable. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
